SIMPLE: topgallant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topgallant
<hw>Top`gal"lant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Situated above the topmast and
below the royal mast; designatb, or pertaining to, the third spars in
order from the deck; <as>as, the <ex>topgallant</ex> mast, yards,
braces, and the like</as>. See <xex>Illustration</xex> of
<er>Ship</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Highest; elevated; splendid.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
consciences of <xex>topgallant</xex> sparks.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Topgallant breeze</b></col>, <cd>a breeze in which the
topgallant sails may properly be carried.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topgallant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Topgallant
<hw>Top`gal"lant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A topgallant mast or sail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Anything elevated or splendid.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toph</ent>⟦br⟧
